## Markdown to HTML Conversion Rules

- `# Heading` â†’ `<h2>` (h1 is reserved for title)
- `## Heading` â†’ `<h3>`
- `**bold**` â†’ `<strong>`
- `*italic*` â†’ `<em>`
- `` `code` `` â†’ `<code>`
- Code blocks â†’ `<pre><code class="language-{lang}">`
- Images â†’ `<img src="../img/{name}" alt="{alt}" width="{width}" loading="lazy">`
- Links â†’ `<a href="{url}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">`
- Lists â†’ `<ul>/<ol>` with `<li>`
- Paragraphs â†’ `<p>`
- Figures with caption â†’ `<figure class="c-post__body-img c-post__body-img--figure"><img><figcaption>`

## Date Formatting

**Spanish:** `{day} de {month-name} de {year}`
Example: `13 de octubre de 2025`

**English:** `{month-name} {day}, {year}`
Example: `October 13, 2025`

**Portuguese:** `{day} de {month-name} de {year}`
Example: `13 de outubro de 2025`

